.TH CS16\-SERVER "8" "May 2026" "cs16\-server" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
cs16\-server \- Counter\-Strike 1.6 Dedicated Server for Linux
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cs16\-server
<\fBstart\fR | \fBstop\fR | \fBrestart\fR | \fBupdate\fR | \fBstatus\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
A script to manage a Counter\-Strike 1.6 server.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBstart\fR
.RS
Start the server.
.RE
.TP
\fBstop\fR
.RS
Stop the server.
.RE
.TP
\fBrestart\fR
.RS
Restart the server.
.RE
.TP
\fBupdate\fR
.RS
Update server files.
.RE
.TP
\fBstatus\fR
.RS
Show server status.
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
\fB# cs16\-server start\fR
.SH CONFIGURATION
\fIcs16\-server.conf\fR file looks like this:
.PP
.RS
hlds_args="\-secure \-pingboost 3 \-maxplayers 32 +sys_ticrate 1024 +sv_lan 0 +map de_dust2 \-dll cstrike/addons/metamod/dlls/metamod.so"
.RE
.PP
\fIhlds_args\fR can be changed to whatever you want; it just passes options to \fBhlds_run\fR.
By default the server is run by user \fIhlds\fR with the account locked.
You need to use \fBsudo \-u hlds bash\fR if you plan to do further configuration in the server directory.
\fBAMX Mod X\fR and \fBMetamod-P\fR are included and enabled by default.
\fBYaPB\fR bots are included too but disabled; if you want to enable them, uncomment the line with \fIyapb.so\fR in the
\fIcstrike/addons/metamod/plugins.ini\fR file.
.SH FILES
.TP
\fI/etc/hlds/cs16\-server.conf\fR
Server config.
.TP
\fI/opt/hlds/cs16\fR
Location of the server files.
